<subSubSection id="3D886557FF91FF9CFF92FAA6FB352C49" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="752D36DCFF91FF9CFF92FAA6FDFB2AA9" blockId="5.[112,648,1327,1484]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">
<materialsCitation id="C5FA3C81FF91FF9CFF92FAA6FDFB2AA9" collectionCode="MOR" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" specimenCode="MOR 1113" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="AA29887EFF91FF9CFF92FAA6FF552A23" box="[113,218,1328,1351]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
. — 
<specimenCode id="25349EA7FF91FF9CFEE1FAB9FEF82A22" box="[258,375,1327,1351]" collectionCode="MOR" country="0" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3ry3-9mkc" name="Museum of the Rockies" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">MOR 1113</specimenCode>
; distal end of right humerus, proximal half of right radius, proximal half and distal end of right ulna. The bones have some distortions due to compression; however, main anatomical details of the specimens are clearly discernible (for detailed discussion of pterosaurian taphonomical bias see 
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFE06FA22FDE62AA9" author="KELLNER A. W. A." box="[485,617,1460,1484]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="1063 - 1084" refId="ref6239" refString="KELLNER A. W. A. 2010. - Comments on Pteranodontidae (Pterosauria, Pterodactyloidea) with the description of two new species. Anais of the Academia Brasileira de Ciencias 82: 1063 - 1084." type="journal article" year="2010">Kellner 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="752D36DCFF91FF9CFF92FA7BFCAB2F95" blockId="5.[111,649,1516,1699]" lastBlockId="5.[675,1211,217,813]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">
EMENDED DIAGNOSIS. 
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFEB7FA79FD9D2961" box="[340,530,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFEB7FA79FEE22961" bold="true" box="[340,365,1519,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFE95FA7AFD9D2961" authorityName="Varricchio" authorityYear="2002" box="[374,530,1516,1540]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Piksi" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barbarulna">Piksi barbarulna</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a minute pterosaur diagnosable by the following autapomorphies: 1) distal margin of humerus oblique relative to the main axis of the shaft, with trochlea strongly distally extended; 2) trochlea bulbous and subspherical; 3) acute and well defined transverse crest connecting the entepicondyle and the lateral ridge that delimitates the olecranal fossa, in posterior view. COMMENTS
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="752D36DCFF91FF9CFD46FF61FB0F2D2B" blockId="5.[675,1211,217,813]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">
The only named pterosaur from the Two Medicine Formation is 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFC80FE81FC5A2E37" authority="Padian, de Ricqles &amp; Horner, 1995" authorityName="Padian, de Ricqles &amp; Horner" authorityYear="1995" class="Reptilia" family="Azhdarchidae" genus="Montanazhdarcho" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterosauria" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFC80FE81FBEB2E54" box="[867,1124,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Montanazhdarcho minor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFB8AFE81FC5A2E37" author="PADIAN K. &amp; DE RICQLES A. J. &amp; HORNER J. R." pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="77 - 84" refId="ref6600" refString="PADIAN K., DE RICQLES A. J. &amp; HORNER J. R. 1995. - Bone histology determines identification of a new fossil taxon of pterosaur (Reptilia: Archosauria). Comptes Rendus de l'Academie des Sciences 320: 77 - 84." type="journal article" year="1995">Padian, de Ricqles &amp; Horner, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFC06FEA1FB3C2E37" author="PADIAN K. &amp; DE RICQLES A. J. &amp; HORNER J. R." box="[997,1203,311,338]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="77 - 84" refId="ref6600" refString="PADIAN K., DE RICQLES A. J. &amp; HORNER J. R. 1995. - Bone histology determines identification of a new fossil taxon of pterosaur (Reptilia: Archosauria). Comptes Rendus de l'Academie des Sciences 320: 77 - 84." type="journal article" year="1995">
Padian 
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFBD9FEAEFBFF2E34" box="[1082,1136,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFD45FEC1FC1F2E14" author="MCGOWAN M. R. &amp; PADIAN K. &amp; DE SOSA M. A. &amp; HAMON R. J." box="[678,912,342,369]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref6427" refString="MCGOWAN M. R., PADIAN K., DE SOSA M. A. &amp; HAMON R. J. 2002. - Description of Montanazhdarcho minor, an azhdarchd pterosaur from the Two Medicine Formation (Campanian) of Montana. Paleobios 22: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2002">
McGowan 
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFCFFFEC1FCC12E15" box="[796,846,342,368]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFC43FEC0FC5C2E15" authorityName="Varricchio" authorityYear="2002" box="[928,979,342,368]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Piksi" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFC43FEC0FC5C2E15" box="[928,979,342,368]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Piksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the latter in having a less distally expanded humerus, a more anteroposteriorly compressed humerus, distal end of the humerus with its external margin longer than the internal one (diagnostic trait of 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFBCAFE43FD622D75" authorityName="Seeley" authorityYear="1870" family="Ornithocheiroidea" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" rank="family">Ornithocheiroidea</taxonomicName>
), more bulbous and larger ectepicondyle, and capitulum shorter and smaller (see additional features in 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFCF8FDA2FCC12D2B" authorityName="Varricchio" authorityYear="2002" box="[795,846,564,590]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Piksi" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFCF8FDA2FCC12D2B" box="[795,846,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Piksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’s generic diagnosis) (
<figureCitation id="EDA92A59FF91FF9CFBD2FDA2FBFD2D2B" box="[1073,1138,564,590]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="3.[113,124,853,870]" captionTargetBox="[144,1203,217,817]" captionTargetId="figure-313@3.[114,1211,165,847]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIG. 2. — Right distal humerus of selected birds and pterosaurs in anterior (top),and distal (bottom) views:A, Azhdarcho Nessov,1984 modified from Averianov (2010); B, Dsungaripterus Young, 1964 modified from Young (1964); C, Piksi Varricchio, 2002 modified from Varricchio (2002); D, Ornithocheiroidea indet.,modified from Averianov et al. (2005);E, Anhanguera Campos &amp; Kellner, 1985, modified from Veldmeijer (2003); F, Montanazhdarcho Padian, de Ricqles &amp; Horner, 1995, modified from McGowen et al. (2002); G, Enantiornithes indet., modified from Hope (2002); H, Ichthyornis dispar Marsh, 1872, modified from Clarke (2004); I, Anas platyrhynchos Linnaeus,1758; J, Limenavis, modified from Clarke &amp; Chiappe (2001). Abbreviations: br, brachial depression; cap, capitulum; dc, dorsal condyle; ent, entepicondyle; pn, pneumatic foramen; tr, trochlea; vc, ventral condyle. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5376784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5376784/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="752D36DCFF91FF9CFD58FDC2FB352C49" blockId="5.[675,1211,217,813]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">
Based on the transversal expansion of the distal humerus of 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFCFDFDE2FCC12DEB" authorityName="Varricchio" authorityYear="2002" box="[798,846,628,654]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Piksi" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFCFDFDE2FCC12DEB" box="[798,846,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Piksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, compared with that of 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFBA2FDE2FC392DC8" authority="Veldmeijer, 2003" authorityName="Veldmeijer" authorityYear="2003" class="Reptilia" family="Anhangueridae" genus="Anhanguera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterosauria" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spielbergi">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFBA2FDE2FC8E2DC8" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Anhanguera spielbergi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFCE6FD05FC392DC8" author="VELDMEIJER A. J." box="[773,950,659,685]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="35 - 139" refId="ref6897" refString="VELDMEIJER A. J. 2003. - Description of Coloborhynchus spielbergi sp. nov. (Pterodactyloidea) from the Albian (Lower Cretaceous) of Brazil. Scripta Geologica 125: 35 - 139." type="journal article" year="2003">Veldmeijer, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFC05FD02FCB92DA8" authority="Kellner &amp; Tomida, 2000" authorityName="Kellner &amp; Tomida" authorityYear="2000" class="Reptilia" family="Anhangueridae" genus="Anhanguera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterosauria" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piscator">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFC05FD02FBC12DC8" box="[998,1102,660,686]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">A. piscator</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFBB1FD05FCB92DA8" author="KELLNER A. W. A. &amp; TOMIDA Y." pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="1 - 135" refId="ref6323" refString="KELLNER A. W. A. &amp; TOMIDA Y. 2000. - Description of a new species of Anhangueridae (Pterodactyloidea) with comments on the pterosaur fauna from the Santana Formation (Aptian-Albian), Northeastern Brazil. National Science Museum Monographs 17: 1 - 135." type="journal article" year="2000">Kellner &amp; Tomida, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFCA1FD25FBB12DA8" author="KELLNER A. W. A. &amp; TOMIDA Y." box="[834,1086,691,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="1 - 135" refId="ref6323" refString="KELLNER A. W. A. &amp; TOMIDA Y. 2000. - Description of a new species of Anhangueridae (Pterodactyloidea) with comments on the pterosaur fauna from the Santana Formation (Aptian-Albian), Northeastern Brazil. National Science Museum Monographs 17: 1 - 135." type="journal article" year="2000">Kellner &amp;Tomida 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFBA4FD25FD532D88" author="VELDMEIJER A. J." pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="35 - 139" refId="ref6897" refString="VELDMEIJER A. J. 2003. - Description of Coloborhynchus spielbergi sp. nov. (Pterodactyloidea) from the Albian (Lower Cretaceous) of Brazil. Scripta Geologica 125: 35 - 139." type="journal article" year="2003">Veldmeijer 2003</bibRefCitation>
) we calculated a wing span of approximately one metre, which posits 
<taxonomicName id="B2924D5FFF91FF9CFC45FD64FC562C69" authorityName="Varricchio" authorityYear="2002" box="[934,985,754,780]" class="Aves" family="Aves (awaiting allocation)" genus="Piksi" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Aves (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47E6EACEFF91FF9CFC45FD64FC562C69" box="[934,985,754,780]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Piksi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a very small pterodactyloid pterosaur (see also 
<bibRefCitation id="11034B2DFF91FF9CFC25FC84FB202C49" author="COSTA F. R. &amp; KELLNER A. W. A." box="[966,1199,786,812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="888" pagination="813 - 818" refId="ref5810" refString="COSTA F. R. &amp; KELLNER A. W. A. 2009. - On two pterosaurian humeri from the Tendaguru beds (Upper Jurassic, Tanzania). Anais da Academia Brasileira de Ciencias 81: 813 - 818." type="journal article" year="2009">
<collectingRegion id="B756F83EFF91FF9CFC25FC84FB8D2C49" box="[966,1026,786,812]" country="Tanzania" name="Pwani" pageId="5" pageNumber="888">Costa</collectingRegion>
&amp; Kellner 2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
